# The data is provided by the website "Reliable Prognosis", rp5.ru
# If you use the data, please indicate the name of the website.

# Interval: Daily Data, includes multiple observation on same day at different times

# Parameters:
	1. T: Air Temperature(degree Celsius) at 2m height above earth surface
	2. P0: Atmospheric Pressure at Weather Station level(millimeters of mercury)
	3. P: Atmospheric Pressure reduced to mean sea level(millimeters of mercury)
	4. Pa: Pressure Tendency: change in atmospheric pressure at last three hours(millimeters of mercury)
	5. U: Relative Humidity(%) at 2m  height above earth's surface
	6. DD: Mean Wind Direction(compass point) at height of 10-12 m above earth's surface over the 10 minute period immediately preceeding the observation
	7. Ff: Mean-wind direction at height of 10-12 meters above earth surface over the 10 minute preiod immediately preceding the observation
	8. ff10: Maximum gust value at height of 10-12m above earth surface over the 10 minute preiod immediately preceding the observation(meters per second)
	9. ff3: Maximum gust value at height of 10-12m above earth surface between the periods of observation
	10. N: Total Cloud Cover
	11. WW: Present weather reported from weather station
	12. W1: Past Weather(weather between the periods of observation)1
	13. W2: Past Weather(weather between the periods of observation)2
	14. Tn: Minimum air temperature(degree Celsius) during past period(not exceeding 12 hrs)
	15. Tx: Maximum air temperature(degree Celsius) during past period(not exceeding 12 hrs)
	16. Cl: Clouds of the genera Stratocumulus, Stratus, Cumulus and Cumulonimbus
	17. Nh: Amount of all Cl cloud present or if no Cl cloud is present, the amount of all Cm cloud present
	18. H: Height of the base of the lowest cloud
	19. Cm:Clouds of genera Altocumulus, Altostratus and Nimbostratus
	20. Ch: Clouds og genera cirrus, cirrocumulus and cirrostratus
	21. VV: Horizontal Visibility(km)
	22. Td: Dew point temperature at height of 2m above earth surface(degree Celsius)
	23. RRR: Amount of precipitation
	24. tR: The time periods during which the specified amount of precipitaion was accumulated
	25. E: State of the ground without snow or measurable ice cover
	26. Tg: The minimum soil surface temperature at night(degC)
	27. E': State of the ground with snow or measurable ice
	28. sss: Snow Depth(cm) 
	
	



